OL,3,CCarrie Johnson warns mothers about
OL,4,Cdehydration after hospitalisation
OL,6,FAdvice on the NHS website tells new
OL,7,Fmothers to drink plenty of fluids and
OL,8,Fto have a drink beside them as they
OL,9,Fsettle down to breastfeed. Water,
OL,10,Flower fat milks, lower sugar or sugar-
OL,11,Ffree drinks are all good choices.
OL,13,FMrs Johnson thanked everyone who has
OL,14,Fhelped them get through a "brutal"
OL,15,Fweek.
OL,17,FShe wrote: "This week has honestly
OL,18,Fbeen brutal. "Mastitis (me), reflux
OL,19,F(her), dehydration (me). What a pair
OL,20,Fwe are!
